         <abstract id="aspace_c79a4b39b08930e8bcf31a88b62892d3">The papers deal chiefly with his ministry in the Third Congregational Church of New Haven and include diaries, account books, clippings, lecture notes, and sermons. The 1,300 sermons make up three-fourths of the papers. His diaries (1850-1864) are largely a record of his ministerial duties, but also contain an account of his brother's death (December 1863) and of his visits to a criminal condemned to be executed (July 1846). The lecture notes were apparently intended for use at the Andover Theological Seminary.</abstract>
         <origination label="creator">
            <persname identifier="http://id.loc.gov/authorities/names/n85158286"
                      rules="aacr"
                      source="naf">
               <part>Cleaveland, Elisha Lord, 1806-1866</part>
            </persname>
         </origination>
    
      </did>
      <prefercite id="aspace_ade4461f95b0f531b43c4f0958c6c9cd">
         <head>Preferred Citation</head>
         <p>Elisha Lord Cleaveland Papers (MS 139). Manuscripts and Archives, Yale University Library.</p>  
      </prefercite>
      <acqinfo id="aspace_625d3466f177ba5700c3d16cb409aa6a">
